description:
Create a base Component class that other components can extend.

## Requirements

Implement a `Component` class with:

1. `constructor(props)` - stores props and initializes empty state object
2. `setState(newState)` - merges newState with existing state and calls `update()`
3. `render()` - returns HTML string (default: `'<div></div>'`)
4. `update()` - calls render() and logs 'Component updated'
5. `mount(container)` - sets element innerHTML to render() result and logs 'Component mounted'

## Expected Usage

```javascript
class Counter extends Component {
    constructor(props) {
        super(props);
        this.state = { count: props.initialCount || 0 };
    }

    render() {
        return `<div>Count: ${this.state.count}</div>`;
    }
}

const counter = new Counter({ initialCount: 5 });
counter.mount(document.body);
counter.setState({ count: 10 }); // Triggers update
```

